<br>
I think the reason everyone thinks this server has so much respect is because of the rotations.  It is human nature to want more, right now.  Who's to say how often you can kill a mob and be considered acting under the &quot;gentlemen's agreement?&quot;  If a guild decided Statue is a main focus for them, and kill him a few spawns in a row, does that mean I get to kill KT 3 times in a row?  Isn't it better that those two guilds equally share both mobs?<br>
<br>
Trak is a 3 day spawn, so I don't see much of a problem with its rotation as long as the guilds promptly kill him.  Sev is more often than not a weekly spawn.  Since he's so easy, the rot has become rather long.  VoF has no green scales banked, and we've gotten a total of 5 since the rotation was created.  There is lots of time in between Sev kills, but I'd imagine every newer guild on the rot is very happy to be on it.<br>
<br>
There may seem to be way too many rotations right now, but I think that's a good thing.  As a guild progresses, it can pick and chose which direction they want to go.  If they have too much on their plate, they can always pass without the worry of never seeing the content in the future.  Rotations are most definitely good. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
