<br>
I think this is the way of the old Luclin and pre-Luclin EQ days. With more and more content out there, it is harder and harder for guilds to wax mobs the instant they are up. Especially on patch days.<br>
<br>
What I have been finding is that the old way of trying to keep it quiet that you were going to make an attempt on a rot mob for fear that the big guild would /gu &quot;OMG get to xyz mob now! We don't want the abc guild on the rot!&quot; is dieing. The new way is to send a /tell to abc guild and say &quot;hey we were hoping for a shot at xyz mob and wanted to know if we could give it a go before you killed?&quot;<br>
<br>
I think you will find that surprisingly enough, the answer will most likely be &quot;Sure thing pal, go ahead.&quot; Of course there will always be exceptions, with very contested 'newer' mobs and some specific 'oldies but goodies'. But for the most part I think you will find what I have said to be true.<br>
<br>
Anyways, that's my opinion and I'm sticking to it.<br>
<br>
Kapen Krunk<br>
